style.name: Kellerbier (Cellar beer) or Zwickelbier - Ale
style.description: These beers are unfiltered German-style Altbier and Kölsch. They are packaged and/or served intentionally with low to moderate amounts of yeast. Products may be filtered and again dosed with yeast in the package, manifesting themselves as bottle conditioned beers or unfiltered beer with yeast present. They will most likely not be clear, and may appear slightly hazy to moderately cloudy. Yeast character, flavor and aroma are desirable, yet should be low to medium but not overpowering the balance and character of malt and hops. Low to moderately low levels of yeast-generated sulfur containing compounds should be apparent in aroma and flavor, and low levels of acetaldehyde or other volatiles normally removed during fermentation may or may not be apparent. The sulfur and acetaldehyde characters should contribute positively to the beer drinking experience. Head retention may not be optimal. The brewer must indicate the classic style on which the entry is based to allow for accurate judging. Beer entries not accompanied by this information will be at a disadvantage during evaluation.

breweries.name: Bayerische Staatsbrauerei Weihenstephan
breweries.description: The Bavarian State Brewery Weihenstephan, founded in 1040, is the oldest existing brewery in the world. As directed by operation of Bavaria it is run as a modern company, which brews beers of the highest quality and successfully sells worldwide in over 40 countries. The unique combination of tradition and science gives the brewer the quality standard "premium bavaricum" and national and international awards for their "Weihenstephan beers."

breweries.name: Boscos Brewing Company
breweries.description:
Located in the historic Overton Square Entertainment District in Midtown Memphis, TN, Boscos believes in using only the freshest products and ingredients in our menu and in our hand-crafted beers.

Each restaurant's menu includes a variety of appetizers, salads, entrees or gourmet pizzas, baked in our brick oven. Signature items include fresh salmon baked on a cedar plank in Boscos brick oven, delicious double-cut pork chop, and a prime cut of steak cooked to perfection.

Boscos has been brewing award-winning handcrafted beers for over 22 years. That experience is evident in both the quality and variety of beers we offer, including the light-bodied, golden Famous Flaming Stone, the amber, crisp Bombay IPA, and our robust, full-bodied stouts and porters. Boscos has a beer to match everyone's tastes and to compliment every delicious dish.

breweries.name: Stuttgarter Lokalbrauerei Calwer-Eck-Bräu
breweries.description:
When the Calwer Eck opened in 1987 it had been Stuttgart's first micro brewery and one among only a few in Germany. Since that day we are brewing the Calwer-Eck-Bräu following our own recipe. It is a bottom-fermented, natural cloudy beer, fresh from the cave. Although it is strongly liable to the German Purity Law dated 1516 it is different to most other beers, since we are not filtering or pasteurizing it but bring it directly from the brewery to your table.

In order to make your stay a most pleasant one, we serve homemade Swabian delicacies with the freshly brewed beer. You can have a look on our traditional micro brewery directly from your seat in the restaurant and you can join a guided tour upon appointment. There are no separate rooms in our pleasant and friendly pub but we´ll be pleased to reserve the requested number of seats for you in one of our most comfortable places of the pub to make your stay with your friends or collegues most enjoyable.

If you come with a larger group of people you have the opportunity to rent the whole restaurant where we will spoil you with our speciality buffets. It will be a pleasure to help you with the combination of your menue and to create the right atmosphere for your stay. Our catering service will bring our home-made delicacies to ever place you want. We will be pleased to handle the whole organisation of your event. Please do not hesitate to contact us in time so that we have all opportunities to meet your requests.

breweries.name: Great Lakes Brewing Company
breweries.description: In the 1870s, Cleveland had 30 breweries. By the early 1980s, the last one had shuttered its doors. So when brothers Patrick and Daniel Conway opened Great Lakes Brewing Company on September 6, 1988, it not only signaled a new era in Cleveland brewing, it was also the first microbrewery in the state of Ohio. And the idea of a craft brewery in Cleveland caught on fast, as curious patrons hurried in for a pint crafted in the styles of old and drawn from the taps of the beautiful Victorian era bar. The company's commitment to sustainable business practices greatly contributed to its early popularity and success. Before long, Great Lakes Brewing Company had become one of Cleveland's most popular destinations for both dining and a fun night out.

breweries.name: Lift Bridge Brewing Co.
breweries.description: Welcome to Lift Bridge Beer Company. Our mission is simple: to create fine beers for you to enjoy! It is our pleasure to supply you with what you need to help you slow down and enjoy life. Whether that is a Farm Girl Saison®, Crosscut Pale Ale™, an American Pale Ale or any of our other seasonal specialties, we want to brew it our way! We hope that through every bottle and tap pull, you can taste: the history of our City, the pride and fun we have in its creation, the uncompromising natural ingredients and brewing process utilized, and ultimately our sincere hope that we have given an experience that makes you proud to be a beer drinker.

data.name: Classic Bioland Export
data.description:
Mild spicy. Lively. Fränkisch - CLASSIC EXPORTS is the amber beer specialty from the Weißenoher monastery brewery.
Unmistakable thanks to its fine spicy aroma. Brewed according to the modern organic standards. Using the best raw materials from the region.
Enjoyment and clarity that you schmeckt.Gebraut should be like a monastery beer. Strong with body and flavor can ask the one for more. Amber and tangy, it presents itself as a unique Bio - specialty beer from Upper Franconia. We brew our Classic according to strict organic guidelines processors which "bring into the field," the Reinheitsgebot (ie the production of malting barley and hops are regulated by organic). Even in the brewery beyond the Reinheitsgebot demands on the quality of raw materials, the craft brewing process and the naturalness of the beer are provided. Only best Biolandmalze, organic aroma hops and our excellent water may be used for brewing. We are pleased that all these ingredients are grown in excellent quality in our immediate vicinity.

data.name: Gold Beach Lager
data.description:
This beer is an award winning unfiltered German style lager, also known as “zwickelbier”.  It is smooth, crisp and refreshing, a product of the longer, cooler fermentation.  Don’t be misled by its light color, this lager has much more flavor than American style lagers.  Brewed with 100% German ingredients, the Hallertau hops are what give its distinct flavor of lemony citrus.  A well carbonated beer that leaves the perfect tingle on your tongue.  With an ABV of 5% this beer is one you’ll want to have a few of!

*2014 Gold Medal --North American Brewers Association

*2014 Gold Medal --Great American Beer Festival Awards

breweries.name: Against The Grain Brewery
breweries.description:
Louisville's only brewer-owned brewery is, like most worthwhile undertakings, the product of dissatisfaction with the status quo. The Louisville area has had a number of quality brewpubs for some time now, but still there was simply not enough beer! Against the Grain is an effort to help solve this problem. We maintain a diverse array of beers covering all of the major categories of beer flavor while generating an endless stream of innovative new brews. In short, everything is "specialty" Boredom will be extremely difficult.

Our food is designed with same philosophy as our brewing. Fresh and interesting smokehouse fare with a gastropub flare lets us bring you the very best flavors to stand alone and to compliment our beers. Regular menu changes allow us to take full advantage of the best seasonal ingredients, our chef's whim, and optimal pairing with our dynamic beer list.

Throw your preconceived notions right the hell out the window. We aren't just another brewpub. We are Against the Grain!

data.name: Helmuth Kellerbier
data.description: We have always childish and thought that all the people in the world are equal. We don’t believe in opposites or “us vs. them” -ideology. We don’t think there is such a big difference between black and white. And we certainly don’t think ours is bigger than yours. Helmuth Kellerbier is a crisp, über-hoppy thirst-quencher based on the European tradition, executed in the New World way – big, bold and loaded with beautiful HOPS! Inspired by the life and times of the legendary “Helmuth of Finland” this beer is a manifestation of all the good things in life, and is dedicated to all the good people in the whole wide world. Let us come together in Peace.

data.name: Kellerbier
data.description: The uniqueness of this beer comes from the yeast. To be precise, a special ale yeast a friendly brewer in England makes Riegele Kellerbier so fruity-fresh. The yeast harmonized unique with the three selected Juramalzsorten (a blend of Munich malt - barley malt kilned red, Pilsener malt (barley malt) and wheat). These three malts are digested and refined in Riegele Two mashing process with the Riegele Spelzentrennung, which gives the beer its distinctive character. A small pinch of Hersbrucker aroma hops gives the beer the finishing touches before it matures in the beer cellars handgeziegelten alone. A piece of craftsmanship!

breweries.name: Brauerei Hofstetten
breweries.description:
Half an hour's walk north of St. Martin in the heart of Mühlviertel, one sees them on a hill
- The brewery Hofstetten

Hofstetten is a private brewery and is in the possession of the family Krammer - since 1849th

For the production of beers Hofstettner raw materials are used only Austrian.

The brewery offers private wells from which water is taken for beer production. This is bedrock water that is filtered through the granite rock, and so only a very low hardness 3-6 ° dH - so the best way to brew beer for good.

The special malts, which are important for the quality of the beers come from the Austrian malt Plohberger (Grieskirchen) and the Stadlauer maltings.

For the pleasant bitterness in the beer aroma and bitter hops makes Mühlviertler that is planted with care by the hop growers from the region and harvested.

There currently are 11 staff employed, they make it possible year 5700 hl best beer brewing and that customer to supply innumerable. Furthermore, as each year about 4,000 visitors a topic of brewing beer and care, as part of a field trip brought closer.

Our goal is to bring our dishes closer to the true beer connoisseur.

style.description: These beers are unfiltered German-style Altbier and Kölsch. They are packaged and/or served intentionally with low to moderate amounts of yeast. Products may be filtered and again dosed with yeast in the package, manifesting themselves as bottle conditioned beers or unfiltered beer with yeast present. They will most likely not be clear, and may appear slightly hazy to moderately cloudy. Yeast character, flavor and aroma are desirable, yet should be low to medium but not overpowering the balance and character of malt and hops. Low to moderately low levels of yeast-generated sulfur containing compounds should be apparent in aroma and flavor, and low levels of acetaldehyde or other volatiles normally removed during fermentation may or may not be apparent. The sulfur and acetaldehyde characters should contribute positively to the beer drinking experience. Head retention may not be optimal. The brewer must indicate the classic style on which the entry is based to allow for accurate judging. Beer entries not accompanied by this information will be at a disadvantage during evaluation.
